  "bib_entries": {
    "78000810": {
      "title": "Not passing flatus on a non-stop flight: Familial cecal volvulus and review of surgical in-flight emergencies",
      "abstract": "Dilatation of the cecum can precipitate its rotation, resulting in a volvulus in individuals who have a mobile cecum. Conditions associated with increased intestinal gas can put predisposed patients at increased risk for cecal volvulus. Drop in the cabin pressure during air travel may cause up to a 30% gas expansion, which might result in cecal dilatation. We report an exceptionally rare occurrence of cecal volvulus in mother and daughter during air travel."
    }
  },
